description: Claudia Sheinbaum has made history as Mexico’s first female president, winning a decisive victory in Sunday’s election. According to Mexico’s official electoral authority, preliminary results show the 61-year-old former mayor of Mexico City securing between 58% and 60% of the vote, leading her main rival, businesswoman Xóchitl Gálvez, by about 30 percentage points. title: Claudia Sheinbaum elected Mexico’s first female president
